<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="196" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1505,2036]" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1649,1675]" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe along all its extension. Anterolateral margin punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with brown punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[1201,1305,1686,1712]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 18K</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin yellow (
<figureCitation box="[488,595,1722,1748]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 18K</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with dark brown stripes (
<figureCitation box="[1085,1188,1722,1748]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 18L</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1564,1588]" captionTargetBox="[166,1417,193,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[151,1436,181,1540]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hypoxys dorsocarinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777072/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 6A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with dorsal rim almost straight, slightly sinuous (
<figureCitation box="[932,1023,1758,1784]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1564,1588]" captionTargetBox="[166,1417,193,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[151,1436,181,1540]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hypoxys dorsocarinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777072/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup reniform, rough, gently concave, adjacent to dorsal rim; ventral margin with short digitiform projection (
<figureCitation box="[1301,1423,1794,1820]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1564,1588]" captionTargetBox="[166,1417,193,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[151,1436,181,1540]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hypoxys dorsocarinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777072/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 6B–C</figureCitation>
); partially visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[508,598,1830,1856]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1564,1588]" captionTargetBox="[166,1417,193,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[151,1436,181,1540]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hypoxys dorsocarinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777072/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Paramere spatulate or remiform, long, strongly projected laterally; dorsal margin acuminated; anterior and posterior lobes little developed (
<figureCitation box="[886,1009,1866,1892]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1564,1588]" captionTargetBox="[166,1417,193,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[151,1436,181,1540]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hypoxys dorsocarinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777072/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 6B–C</figureCitation>
); stalk medially with longitudinal low carina directed toward anterior lobe, but ending far from its apex. Proctiger with dorsolateral tufts of long setae separated by medial high keel; posterior face rounded (
<figureCitation box="[776,901,1938,1964]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1564,1588]" captionTargetBox="[166,1417,193,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[151,1436,181,1540]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hypoxys dorsocarinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777072/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 6B–D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim medial excavation in “V”; expansion developed, rounded, and surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view; expansions curved ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[159,283,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1564,1588]" captionTargetBox="[166,1417,193,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[151,1436,181,1540]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hypoxys dorsocarinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777072/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 6B–D</figureCitation>
). Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
